{"article_id":"ukZjsQUdEb7TeLUh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Obama administration put on a full-court press Sunday","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"to defend the deal","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"the U.S. and key allies struck","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"to try to halt Iran ' s burgeoning nuclear program -","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"but the White House faces a tough sell with members of Congress","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"who criticized the terms","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"and said","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"they ' ll still press for even tighter sanctions on the Islamic republic .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"President Obama spoke to Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu ,","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"who called the agreement a \" historic mistake. \"","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"The American leader assured Mr. Netanyahu","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"that the deal is just a first step ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"and that the U.S. remains firmly committed to Israel ' s interests .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"But in Washington , many Republicans and Democrats shared Mr. Netanyahu ' s view ,","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Iran gets far more","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"than it ' s giving","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"and that the deal only suspends ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"rather than ends , Iran ' s nuclear ambitions .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Secretary of State John F. Kerry defended the agreement ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"reached early Sunday morning in Geneva after months of secret negotiations ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"it gives Iran a six-month window","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to prove","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"it is serious about freezing its weapons program .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"He also assured Capitol Hill","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"if the Islamic republic backslides ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"the world can reimpose stiff sanctions","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"- and could resort to military action .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"\" You can ' t get everything in the first step .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"You have to go down the process here , \"","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Mr. Kerry said on CBS ' \" Face the Nation. \"","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"\" The fact is that what we ' ve done is lock components of their program in place","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"and actually roll some of them backwards . \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Capitol Hill was less than convinced ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"with both Republicans and Democrats saying","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"they feared","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"the deal was laden with carrots","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"and lacking in sticks .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":3},{"id":41,"text":"Career diplomat William Burns steered the Iran talks quietly though rounds of negotiations","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"\" You have now given them a permission slip","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"to continue enrichment , \"","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Rep. Mike Rogers , Michigan Republican , chairman of the House intelligence committee , told CNN ' s \" State of the Union \" program .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"And Sen. Bob Corker , the ranking Republican on the Senate Foreign Relations Committee , said","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s track record doesn ' t give him confidence","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that this administration will be able to see through the agreement .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"\" This administration is long on announcements but very short on follow-through , \"","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"the Tennessee Republican said on \" Fox News Sunday . \"","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Congress is away from Washington for a two-week Thanksgiving vacation ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"but","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"when it returns ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"the Senate has the critical defense policy bill pending .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"There will be a major push by Republicans and some Democrats","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"to add stricter sanctions on Iran to that legislation as a way","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"of showing displeasure with the deal","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and trying to stiffen Mr. Obama ' s spine in the negotiations .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Meanwhile , the two sides in the agreement will go back to the table","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"to work out the next deal .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"The White House said Sunday afternoon","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"that there is no set timetable for the next round of talks ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"though a spokesman said","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"the administration is \" eager \" to get to work .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Sunday ' s deal was struck between Iran and the five permanent members of the U.N. Security Council and Germany ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"which combined refer to themselves as the P5 plus 1 .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"Talks had apparently been going on for months ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"but kicked into a higher gear","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"after Hassan Rouhani won Iran ' s presidential elections","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"and took office in August","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"after campaigning on a platform of a willingness","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"to engage with the West .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"The White House pointed out","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that Mr. Obama had campaigned in 2008 on engaging in direct negotiations with adversary nations","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"including Iran ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"this deal was struck in that vein .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Late Saturday night at the White House , Mr. Obama said","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"the tentative pact will \" cut off Iran ' s most likely paths to a bomb \"","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"and that the United States and its partners will not proceed with new sanctions","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that would scuttle the deal .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Mr. Kerry said","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"that the choice for the U.S. was between taking this deal ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"or waiting","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"and potentially letting Iran progress further .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"the latter was the option","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"the Bush administration took ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"and in the 10 years since , Iran went from fewer than 200 centrifuges to 19,000 ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"putting the nation much closer to a weapon .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"The six-month interim deal offers Iran relief from sanctions","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"that will be worth billions of dollars to the regime ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"in exchange for granting access to Iranian nuclear sites and a promise by that nation","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"to reduce its enrichment of uranium .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Israel and other critics of the deal had wanted any agreement to undo Iran ' s nuclear program .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Instead , the package rolls back","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"but doesn ' t eliminate Iran ' s stockpile of enriched material","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"by suspending all enrichment of uranium over 5 percent ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"and forcing the country to degrade its supply of 20 percent enriched uranium .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"Iran also agreed not to add any centrifuges ,","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"used to enrich uranium ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"to its supply ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"but it can replace those","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that become inoperable .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"The nation also agreed not to begin operating the Arak reactor ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"which was considered to be a shortcut to the plutonium","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"needed for a nuclear weapon .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Mr. Kerry said","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"degrading Iran ' s capability means","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"if the country ' s leaders decided to break the deal","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"and try to create a bomb ,","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"it would take longer to do it .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"\" That means","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"whereas Iran today has about 200 kilograms of 20 percent enriched uranium ,","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"they could readily be enriched towards a nuclear weapon .","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"In six months , Iran will have zero - zero , \"","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"In return , the countries","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"that imposed sanctions","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"will allow Iran to sell oil","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"and collect $ 4.2 billion on the sale ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"and will lower sanctions","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"that restricted the import of gold and materials for some industries , such as automobile manufacturing .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"Mr. Kerry said","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"even with the sanctions","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"that will remain in place ,","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"Iran will still lose $ 25 billion in oil revenue during the six-month period of the deal .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"Opponents , though , said","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"the deal walks back key U.S. demands","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"- particularly in allowing Iran to enrich uranium .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"They said","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"the amount of time","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"added to an Iranian \" breakout , \" or production of a full bomb ,","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"has only been increased by several months .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"And they fretted","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"that beginning to dismantle sanctions will make it harder to reimpose them","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"- or to enhance them later -","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"should Iran backslide .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"\" Iran simply freezes its nuclear capabilities","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"while we reduce the sanctions , \"","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"said Sen. Charles E. Schumer , New York Democrat .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"\" It was strong sanctions , not the goodness of the hearts of the Iranian leaders , that brought Iran to the table ,","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"and any reduction relieves the psychological pressure of future sanctions","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"and gives them hope","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"that they will be able to gain nuclear weapon capability","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"while further sanctions are reduced . \"","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"Mr. Schumer said","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"the terms of the deal are so bad","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"that it actually makes it more likely than ever that Congress will pass legislation","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"stiffening the sanctions on Iran .","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"But White House spokesman Josh Earnest played down that possibility ,","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"that he believed","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Congress would hold off on stricter sanctions","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"and give Mr. Obama room","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"to operate .","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"He also said","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"if the U.S. imposes deeper unilateral sanctions ,","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"if could fracture the front","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"that Mr. Obama has worked to maintain , particularly with Russia and China .","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"\" The concern is that","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"rather than capitalizing on the diplomatic window","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"that ' s opened up ,","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"doubling down on sanctions at this point would actually undermine the international coalition","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"that we ' ve built , \"","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"Mr . Earnest said .","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"\" That is why we have urged Congress to act strategically ,","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"as they have thus far ,","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"to bring pressure on the Iranian regime ,","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"to reach a diplomatic solution ,","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"but do that in a way","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"that it doesn ' t actually undermine the broad international pressure","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"that ' s been brought to bear . \"","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":347,"left":213,"right":346,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":213,"left":181,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":177,"right":180,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":0,"right":176,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":4,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":5,"right":178,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":178,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":212,"left":185,"right":211,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":185,"left":182,"right":184,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":182,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":10,"right":183,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":183,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":211,"left":190,"right":210,"relation":"joint","nucle